  "source_id": "iron-deficiency-anemia",
  "name": "Iron Deficiency Anemia - Low Hemoglobin Lab Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find anemic patients via low hemoglobin (<12 g/dL). First Hgb lab test. Includes Path D (low Hgb without formal IDA dx).",
  "prompt": "Find patients with hemoglobin results below 12 g/dL.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients with low hemoglobin.",
    "broad": "Find patients with hemoglobin measurements below 12 g/dL — reflective of anemia (normal F: 12-16, M: 14-18 g/dL).",
    "expert": "I need to identify patients with laboratory evidence of anemia via a low hemoglobin measurement. Search Observation resources for the hemoglobin in blood test, coded in LOINC, and filter to results below the conventional anemia cutoff — approximately 12 g/dL — using a less-than value-quantity filter. This approach captures patients in Path D: those with objectively low hemoglobin who may not have a formal iron deficiency anemia diagnosis recorded."
  },
  "metadata": {
    "implementation_guide": "US Core 5.0.0",
    "algorithm_path": "labs-path",
